data.name: commenting_description
data.value: The Law Editing Service is prepared by the Ministry of Justice to ensure that the draft policies, strategies, laws (proclamations, regulations, guidelines) are prepared in accordance with the Constitution, international agreements accepted by our country, other national laws and follow the principles of law drafting. General work is the work of drafting examination and preparation of comments carried out by the department. When a request for legal correction is submitted, it is expected from the requesting government institution to provide a policy prepared on the issue, a preliminary study on the issue, a copy of the draft law in Amharic and English, and an explanation of the draft law in Word format in soft copy and hard copy.

data.name: Inspection_Followup_description
data.value: All government institutions are required by law to give information on the contracts they enter and all civil cases they might have whatsoever its nature is. So as to know the number of cases they have and also to inspect whether these cases are being properly handled by the institutions in a manner that maintains the public interest, the CJADG visits government institutions in person. Based on the findings, CJADG gives recommendations and follow up the execution of the recommendations. It also directly engages in handling the cases that it selects.

data.name: legal_advice_description
data.value: The CJDG takes the principal advisory role in civil, commercial and investment related legal matters given to the Ministry of Justice. Accordingly, it provides legal advice to the federal, Addis Ababa and Dire Dawa government institutions including public enterprises pursuant to Proclamation No. 943/2016. Legal advice is also among the services the CJADG gives to those people including, children, women, elderly, victims of a crime, etc, who does not have sufficient finance to institute suites before federal courts.

data.name: legal_drafting_description
data.value: One of the responsibilities assigned to the Ministry of Justice is the drafting of laws or drafting of laws, which is carried out by the Directorate General of Legal Research, Drafting and Compilation. It can be a policy, strategy, law (decree, regulation or directive). In order to get the services of the Ministry of Justice, government institutions that want to draft a law for them, submit a request for a law draft to get the service, if there is a policy document prepared on the issue, a study document on the issue, and if a draft law is being prepared, the number of the law to be amended or the rule or directive of the draft law, the mother law (authority to issue the rule or directive Proclamation No.) are mentioned and notified as a condition.

data.name: Mandates_Description
data.value:
Mandates

Strategies

1.       Continuing the reform of the institution and building up implementation capacity.

2.       Providing effective, efficient, accessible and predictable justice,

3.       Enabling drafts, codification and consolidation of law supported by research and study.

4.       Giving prior to the activities on the prevention of affiances endangering the constitution, constitutional order and public interest and deterring criminals before the court.

5.       Establishing a system of compensation for victims of crime in civil affairs.

6.       Enabling prisoners abide in law and professional with proper handling and protection of human rights.

7.       Making legal research and study and enhancing awareness of the community in protection of human rights, strengthening the rule of law and supporting for good governance and development. 

8.       Creation public capacity and arrangement, which respect and enforce the law and the system through proving public awareness level by level.

9.       Creating public legal awareness through accelerated dissemination of law.

10.   Enhancing the role of Mass and professional association’s stake holders in the building up of good governance and democratization system.

11.   Ensuring and following up the implementation of the courts decisions

12.   Ensuring whether there are respected legal rights and interests of women. Youth, children, disabled and people who are living with HIV/AIDS.

13.   Establishing a system which ensures professional competence and codes of conduct of advocates to enhance their role in the justice system, making complete and change in to proactive the registration system.

14.   Fully changed in to practice the system of documents authentication and registration.

data.name: mission_detail
data.value: Respecting and upholding the rule of law and human rights; By preventing crime, ensuring peace and security and protecting the interests of the government and the people; Providing accessible, efficient, fair and effective justice services that have won public disapproval.
data.comment: Respecting and upholding the rule of law and human rights; By preventing crime, ensuring peace and security and protecting the interests of the government and the people; Providing accessible, efficient, fair and effective justice services that have won public disapproval.

data.name: Mission_Vision_Detail
data.value:
Mission

“ To see the Federal Attorney General Institution that ensures respect of rule of law and win public and state beliefs with participation of the people in 2024/25.”

 

Vision

“Working as principal advisor and representative of the federal government regarding law; undertake legal reform studies, drafting laws, disseminations and enforcing criminal law; ensuring the implementation of federal laws enacted by the federal government and the consistency of their implementations; Performing as central authority of international relations regarding law, follow up implementation of national human rights action plan; offering the relevant legal aid for citizens who do not have financial capacity and needs special attention; enforcing civil interest of the federal government and the public; supervise and administer advocates licensing; enhancing participations of the society and stake holders; ensuring rule of law by respecting and enforcing the constitution and constitutional order.”

Values

  • Strong belief on rule of law
  • Prioritizing public and government interest
  • Participatory working condition sprit
  • Transparency and accountability
  • Detest corruption and malpractices
  • Readiness for change
  • Working in team sprit
  • Sense of service giving
  • Fairness
  • Efficiency and effectiveness
  • Coordination
  • Rendering expedition, qualified and effective services

data.name: paragraph_one
data.value: Ministry of Justice: Our country's democracy and justice, rapid and continuous development, and the people's greater benefit cannot be ensured without the rule of law and the practical activities of the justice sector. It will be remembered that the history of our country's justice sector has been plagued by deep-rooted problems of law and procedure as well as attitudes and was a captive of bullies.

data.name: paragraph_three
data.value: The Ministry of Justice is carrying out its national mission at a higher level than ever before by creating a favorable environment for wide and universal cooperation to bring about the national journey of change, respecting and enforcing the judicial and constitutional system, ensuring the rule of law, ensuring justice, and ensuring the human and democratic rights of citizens. .

data.name: paragraph_two
data.value: In the new phase of change that has started, our institution has carried out, and is still carrying out, many basic reform activities by carrying out law and justice reform and improving operational problems, by adjusting the treatment of legal prisoners in terms of human rights, ensuring efficient, fair and effective access to justice in institutional services.

data.name: recomendation_dashboard_description
data.value: The Ministry of Justice makes recommendations to different Ethiopina Ministry offices to promote effectiveness, efficiency, economy, and integrity of all programs and operations, including those performed by its contractors and grantees. Recommendations are considered resolved when Ministry offices and Ministry agree on the required corrective actions. After the agreed-upon corrective actions have been completed, the recommendations are considered closed. This Recommendation Dashboard provides the status of Ministry of Justice recommendations.

data.name: terms_conditions
data.value:
The civil service client should attach a brief explanation to the text to be submitted first, as appropriate, provide an explanation explaining the procedures of the case, prohibited and non-added cases, reasons, strengths and weaknesses, and the level reached, etc. Accordingly:

  1. Service related to accountability, to organize text, e-mail sound, image, moving image, etc. information and evidence in their respective categories and in chronological order and keep evidence when requested to be submitted.
  2. To notify in writing a representative who has an understanding of the matter presented, who can respond to questions asked during the service delivery process and who can make decisions on behalf of the institution on behalf of the institution; 
  3. To immediately inform about events, new information and evidence regarding the matter,
  4. To provide explanations to the questions asked from the Ministry of Justice during the service delivery process, to carry out the orders and decisions given and to perform other related activities within the time limits set;
  5. Not to attempt to resolve the matter through negotiation or any other administrative means without the knowledge of the Ministry of Justice from the time the service began to be provided.
  6. To cover the expenses necessary for the provision of services, to make the physical presence of the institution's leaders or experts necessary, as well as to carry out other orders given according to other relevant instructions, I agree and understand that failure to fulfill the prescribed responsibilities will result in termination of service by the Ministry of Justice.
